<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="R2-022" project="SprkChat Platform Enhancement R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Open in Word Endpoint — Markdown to DOCX, SPE Upload, Word Online URL</title>
    <status>pending</status>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, api</tags>
    <estimated-effort>medium</estimated-effort>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>BFF API code implementation — creates a new Minimal API endpoint integrating DocxExportService, SpeFileStore upload, and Word Online URL construction; FR-15 requirement; multiple ADRs apply</rigor-reason>
    <dependencies>[006]</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create a new BFF API endpoint that converts analysis output (markdown) to a DOCX file, uploads
    it to the matter's SPE container, and returns a Word Online URL for opening in Word directly.

    **Endpoint**: `POST /api/ai/chat/export/word`
    - Body:
      ```json
      {
        "content": "# Analysis Title\n\nMarkdown content...",
        "filename": "Analysis-2026-03-17.docx",
        "sessionId": "...",
        "metadata": { "matterName": "...", "analysisDate": "..." }
      }
      ```
    - Returns `201 Created`:
      ```json
      {
        "speFileId": "...",
        "filename": "Analysis-2026-03-17.docx",
        "wordOnlineUrl": "https://[tenant].sharepoint.com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc={fileId}",
        "sizeBytes": N,
        "generatedAt": "..."
      }
      ```

    **Processing pipeline**:
    1. Validate request: content must be non-empty; filename must end in `.docx`
    2. Resolve `ChatHostContext` from the session to get SPE container ID
    3. Call `DocxExportService.GenerateAsync(content, filename, metadata)` to produce a .docx byte array
       - Extend `DocxExportService` if needed to support markdown-to-DOCX conversion (existing service
         may already generate DOCX via OpenXML SDK — verify and extend for markdown input)
    4. Upload .docx byte array to SPE container via `SpeFileStore.UploadFileAsync(containerId, filename, bytes, "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document")`
    5. Construct Word Online URL: `https://{tenantSharePointDomain}/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc={speFileId}`
    6. Return 201 Created with the response body

    **DocxExportService extension**: The existing `DocxExportService` likely generates DOCX from
    structured data. Extend it with a `GenerateFromMarkdownAsync(string markdown, string title)` method
    that:
    - Parses markdown using a lightweight approach (no need for a full markdown parser — just handle
      headings #/##/###, bold **text**, and paragraph breaks)
    - Maps to OpenXML paragraph styles (Heading1, Heading2, Normal)
    - Applies the Spaarke document template (check if a template .docx exists in the project)

    **Authorization**: `ChatSessionAuthorizationFilter` — session must belong to the caller.
    **Rate limiting**: Apply ADR-016 rate limiting.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer with Azure AI and Minimal API expertise</role>

  <goal>
    A working `POST /api/ai/chat/export/word` endpoint that generates a DOCX from markdown content,
    uploads it to the matter's SPE container, and returns a Word Online URL. User clicks "Open in Word"
    button → Word Online opens with formatted analysis content (FR-15).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="Project specification — FR-15 (Open in Word), Word Online URL construction">projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="Project AI context — SpeFileStore pattern, ChatHostContext flow, MUST rules">projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="DocxExportService — existing DOCX generation service to extend">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Export/DocxExportService.cs</file>
    <file purpose="SpeFileStore facade — upload method and container resolution">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Storage/SpeFileStore.cs</file>
    <file purpose="SPE persistence endpoint from R2-014 — URL construction pattern reference">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatDocumentEndpoints.cs</file>
    <file purpose="Minimal API endpoint definition pattern">../.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-definition.md</file>
    <file purpose="Authorization endpoint filter pattern">../.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-filters.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">MUST use Minimal API pattern — no MVC controllers</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-007">MUST use SpeFileStore.UploadFileAsync for the SPE upload — MUST NOT call Microsoft Graph SDK directly</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">MUST apply authorization endpoint filter for session ownership verification</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">MUST flow ChatHostContext for SPE container ID resolution — container ID MUST NOT be hardcoded</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec assumption">"Basic Spaarke document template (header/footer/logo) exists or will be created during implementation" — if a template does not exist, create a minimal one as part of this task</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">MUST use the existing DocxExportService (OpenXML SDK) — MUST NOT introduce a new DOCX generation library</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Export/DocxExportService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Storage/SpeFileStore.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatDocumentEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-definition.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-filters.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-001-minimal-api.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-007-spefilestore.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-008-endpoint-filters.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern>Word Online URL construction: `https://{tenantSharePointHostname}/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc={speFileId}&amp;action=default` where tenantSharePointHostname comes from ChatHostContext or appsettings</pattern>
      <pattern>OpenXML heading paragraph: `new Paragraph(new ParagraphProperties(new ParagraphStyleId { Val = "Heading1" }), new Run(new Text(headingText)))` — use OpenXML SDK style IDs for heading levels</pattern>
      <pattern>Markdown parsing for DOCX: simple line-by-line: if line starts with `# ` → Heading1, `## ` → Heading2, `### ` → Heading3, else Normal paragraph; handle `**bold**` via Run properties</pattern>
      <pattern>SpeFileStore upload returns a file metadata object with the SPE file ID — use this ID in the Word Online URL construction</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      "Open in Word" is a key UX feature for legal professionals who want to refine AI-generated
      analysis in Microsoft Word Online. The workflow is:
      1. AI generates analysis in SprkChat
      2. User clicks "Open in Word" button (Phase 3 Task R2-044)
      3. Frontend calls this BFF endpoint with the chat message content as markdown
      4. BFF generates .docx, uploads to matter's SPE container
      5. BFF returns Word Online URL
      6. Frontend opens the URL in a new tab

      The `DocxExportService` already exists from R1 — it generates DOCX for some purpose. Extending
      it for markdown input means adding a `GenerateFromMarkdownAsync` method that handles the
      common markdown patterns used in AI-generated analysis: headings, bold, paragraphs, numbered
      lists, and bullet lists.

      Word Online requires the file to be in a SharePoint site the user has access to. SPE containers
      associated with matter records satisfy this requirement — the user's Dataverse security role
      already governs SPE access for their matters.

      From `notes/014-spe-persistence-urls.md` (R2-014 output): the Word Online URL pattern and
      SPE file ID format should already be documented — reference it before implementing step 5.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      Depends on Task R2-006 (Phase 1 deployment complete). Sequential. Safe to run after R2-021.
      Task R2-024 (rate limiting) and R2-057 (Open in Word integration) depend on this task.
      Own files: new Word export endpoint handler file, `DocxExportService.cs` (markdown extension).
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Read `DocxExportService.cs` to understand the current DOCX generation implementation and OpenXML SDK usage patterns</step>
    <step order="1">Read `SpeFileStore.cs` and `notes/014-spe-persistence-urls.md` (if exists from R2-014) for Word Online URL construction pattern</step>
    <step order="2">Verify or create the Spaarke DOCX template: check for an existing template file in `Resources/` or `Assets/` — if none exists, create a minimal template with Spaarke header/footer text</step>
    <step order="3">Add `GenerateFromMarkdownAsync(string markdown, string title, ExportMetadata metadata)` method to `DocxExportService`</step>
    <step order="4">Implement markdown-to-OpenXML conversion: handle `#`/`##`/`###` headings, `**bold**`, bullet lists (`- item`), numbered lists (`1. item`), and plain paragraphs</step>
    <step order="5">Create `WordExportRequest` and `WordExportResponse` models</step>
    <step order="6">Create the Word export endpoint handler (new file `ChatWordExportEndpoints.cs` or addition to existing endpoint file)</step>
    <step order="7">Implement the 5-step pipeline: validate → resolve context → generate DOCX → upload to SPE → construct Word Online URL</step>
    <step order="8">Apply authorization endpoint filter and rate limiting</step>
    <step order="9">Register the endpoint in the application</step>
    <step order="10">Run `dotnet build` and verify no errors</step>
    <step order="11">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task R2-022 status to completed (🔲 → ✅)</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
